From fde7124d6351a1c9ba512fc6306256c20357e06b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaya <amaya.mali3@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 03:27:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(toast): add status icons (Information/Success/Error) per
 Figma

Update the Toast notification component to match the Sage Component kit
design (Figma node 215-108):

- Add inline SVG status icons in the top-left:
  - Information: blue circle with 'i'
  - Success:     green circle with checkmark
  - Error:       red triangle with '!'
- Replace the 'default' state name with 'information'
  ('default' is kept as a backwards-compatible alias)
- Update background colors:
  - Information: #E0F4FF (light blue)
  - Success:     #E2FBDC (pale green)
  - Error:       #FFE5E0 (warm peach)
- Remove the 4px left accent border (no longer in the design)
- Add a '+' icon to the action button and switch it to a tertiary
  pill (0.5px border + primary text color)
- Refresh Storybook stories to use the new state names and demo
  Information/Success/Error variants

Figma: https://www.figma.com/design/5TMUAOp35jOOKBNNqEo32Z/Sage-Component-kit?node-id=215-108
